com.wikitude.architect
Interface ArchitectView.ArchitectUrlListener

Enclosing class:
ArchitectView
public static interface ArchitectView.ArchitectUrlListener

The ArchitectUrlListener offers the native app the possibility to react on events that are triggered inside the ARchitect World. To initiate such an event, the ARchitect World simply has to make an request for an url with the "architectsdk" as protocol. E.g.: architectsdk://opendetails?id=123 A registered ArchitectUrlHandler receives all requested "architectsdk://" urls and will therefore be able to parse the url and parameters to react accordingly.
